main event: A witness spotted a metallic, cigar-shaped object over Jewfish Creek, Florida in 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared to be turning and drifting, making gradual turns.
There were two observers who saw the object from different locations.
The object was described as being as long as a blimp, but not as thick.
The object was metallic and silvery in color.
The object was seen for about 10 minutes before it gradually faded out of sight.
